<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A66FF9AFF4CFD6FEDDAFCC0" box="[151,403,762,787]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A66FF9AFF4CFD6FEDDAFCC0" blockId="25.[151,498,727,787]" box="[151,403,762,787]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFF4CFD6FECADFCC0" box="[151,228,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
a–h 15g–i, 19c.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A66FF9AFF4CFCD7E8B5FBE1" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A66FF9AFF4CFCD7E8B5FBE1" blockId="25.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFF4CFCD7ED43FC88" bold="true" box="[151,266,834,859]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Crown short; two pairs of small wedge-shaped dark brown markings apically and subapically. Subgenital plate obovate; ratio of length to width 0.87–1.28. Aedeagal shaft apex anterodorsally with single tooth, subapex laterally with short paired tooth; uniformly curved posterodorsally, tubular; dorsal apodeme in dorsal view transverse bar-shape; aedeagal process long, subparallel, straight, acuminate, distal third acanthoid. Style apophysis acutely triangular, dorsomedially with narrow, right-angled digitate process. Connective with midsection concave, arms short. Pygofer lobe apex with sclerotized, acuminate, ventroposteriad process. Tergite X rectangular; tubular in dorsal view, apex ventrally with short, sclerotized, digitate, posteriad process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A66FF9AFF1CFBABEEF7FBA8" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A66FF9AFF1CFBABEEF7FBA8" blockId="25.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFF1CFBABED0FFB84" bold="true" box="[199,326,1086,1111]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named for the three teeth on the apex and subapex of the aedeagal shaft, with two nouns in apposition, Greek, three, 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFE69FBF1EDACFBA8" box="[434,485,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">trias</emphasis>
, and tooth, 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFDB1FBF7EEF7FBA8" box="[618,702,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">akaina.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A66FF9AFF1CFB13EDEBF808" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A66FF9AFF1CFB13EDFAFAD8" blockId="25.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFF1CFB13ED4DFB4C" bold="true" box="[199,260,1158,1183]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFECAFB13EE59FB4C" bold="true" box="[273,528,1158,1183]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">External morphology</emphasis>
. Specimens stramineous, with small dark brown to black marking submarginally on apex of crown (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFEB3FB3FEDB5FB10" box="[360,508,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Figs 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A66FF9AFE7BFB3FED85FB10" box="[416,460,1194,1219]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="g" value="15.0">15g</quantity>
, 
<date id="FFF910217A66FF9AFE03FB3FEDB5FB10" box="[472,508,1194,1219]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" value="2015-01">15i</date>
</figureCitation>
) or large marks with transvers line across disc (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFBC9FB3FE83DFB10" box="[1042,1140,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 15h</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with two pairs of circular brown marks near posterior margin of eye. Tegmina with brown marks in some cells and most veins embrowned (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFEF1FB67ED36FAD8" box="[298,383,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 15</figureCitation>
g–i).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A66FF9AFF1CFA83EF58FAA4" blockId="25.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFF1CFA83ED4DFAFC" bold="true" box="[199,260,1302,1327]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFEC8FA83ED8BFAFC" bold="true" box="[275,450,1302,1327]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Measurements</emphasis>
. Overall length 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A66FF9AFDA7FA83EF6DFAFD" box="[636,804,1302,1327]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.83" metricValueMax="4.86" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="4.83" valueMax="4.86" valueMin="4.8">4.80–4.86 mm</quantity>
; crown length 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A66FF9AFC16FA82E83CFAFD" box="[973,1141,1303,1327]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3999999999999995" metricValueMax="4.699999999999999" metricValueMin="4.1" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="0.43999999999999995" valueMax="0.47" valueMin="0.41">0.41–0.47 mm</quantity>
; crown length next to eye 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A66FF9AFF4CFAAEED0BFA81" box="[151,322,1339,1363]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="0.375" valueMax="0.38" valueMin="0.37">0.37–0.38 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A66FF9AFDC4FAAFEE82FA81" box="[543,715,1338,1363]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="0.535" valueMax="0.55" valueMin="0.52">0.52–0.55 mm</quantity>
; head width 1.3 8– 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A66FF9AFC73FAAEE85CFA81" box="[936,1045,1339,1363]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.44" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="1.44">1.44 mm</quantity>
; pronotum width 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A66FF9AFB37FAAEE9D1FA81" box="[1260,1432,1339,1363]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3599999999999999" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.32" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="1.3599999999999999" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.32">1.32–1.40 mm</quantity>
; ocellus diameter 42.0 µm; interocellar distance 56.0 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A66FF9AFF1CFA17E8F0F864" blockId="25.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFF1CFA17ED4DFA48" bold="true" box="[199,260,1410,1435]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFECFFA17EDCBFA48" bold="true" box="[276,386,1410,1435]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Genital capsule short in lateral view, large lobulate anterior apodeme in Willowmore and Beaufort West specimens (as in 
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFDDBFA33EED0FA6C" box="[512,665,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 11a, 11b</figureCitation>
), absent in Oudtshoorn specimen (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFBFBFA33E8C8FA6C" box="[1056,1153,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 14a</figureCitation>
). Tergite X long, tubular, with sclerotized process on ventroposterior margin (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFD3AFA5FEF08FA30" box="[737,833,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 14a</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate extending beyond posterior margin of pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFEA8FA7BEDA9F9D4" box="[371,480,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 14b</figureCitation>
). Pygofer lobe with wide, triangular base, apex with sclerotized, acuminate, ventroposteriad process; macrosetae dorsomedially, up to 15 long macrosetae, about 8 shorter macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFAB4F987EC8DF99C" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 14b</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with medial margin straight, adjacent margins subparallel; lateral margin at base concave; distally curvate, posterior margin curvate; macrosetae grouped near apex, up to 20 macrosetae, fine setae apically and laterally (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFEECF9EBEDD2F944" box="[311,411,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 14c</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with ratio of length to greatest width 0.87–1.28 (n=3). Aedeagus with shaft tubular, curvate, apex with single, anterodorsal tooth and subapically with paired lateral tooth (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFB2CF937E9C6F968" box="[1271,1423,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 14e, 14f</figureCitation>
); ventrodistal half of shaft with membranous ridge surrounding gonopore (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFC16F953E864F90C" box="[973,1069,1734,1759]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 14e</figureCitation>
); dorsal apodeme in lateral view short, in dorsal view transverse with short arms (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFD31F97FEF04F8D0" box="[746,845,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 14f</figureCitation>
), atrium elongated, articulated with connective at midsection, aedeagal paraphysis elongate, longer than shaft, tubular, apex acuminate or with small barb, distal third acanthoid (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFEC9F8A7EDE7F898" box="[274,430,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 14d, 14e</figureCitation>
). Style with apophysis weakly sclerotized, straight, broadly acuminate, directed posteriad, dorsally at mid-section with digitate, right-angled process, process as long as width across mid-section; preapical lobe rounded, preapical angle acute; anterior medial arm short, anterior lateral arm elongate (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFB3CF8EFE9C6F840" box="[1255,1423,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Figs 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A66FF9AFAFEF8EEE918F840" box="[1317,1361,1915,1939]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.4" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="g" value="14.0">14g</quantity>
, 14h
</figureCitation>
). Connective with mid-section concave, long, arms short, right-angled to mid-section (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFB94F80BE8E5F864" box="[1103,1196,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,668,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,668,1709]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14a–h. Discolopeus tetracaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, ventrally, laterally and dorsally respectively; g. Style, dorsally; h. Style apophysis, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626839/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 14f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
