<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A65FF99FF1CFE91EFF4FDEF" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A65FF99FF1CFE91EFF4FDEF" blockId="26.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A65FF99FF1CFE91ED7DFECE" bold="true" box="[199,308,260,285]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Remarks</emphasis>
. Of the specimens examined, from Beaufort West (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A65FF99FC59FE91EF97FECE" box="[898,990,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<date id="FFF910217A65FF99FC63FE91EF97FECE" box="[952,990,260,285]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" value="2015-01">15i</date>
</figureCitation>
), Rust en Vrede near Oudtshoorn (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A65FF99FAB4FE91EC8BFE93" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A65FF99FF4CFEB2EC8BFE93" box="[151,194,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" unit="g" value="15.0">15g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) and Willowmore (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A65FF99FE45FEB2EE49FE93" box="[414,512,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Fig. 15h</figureCitation>
), all were dissected previously, so the original position of the aedeagus within the genital capsule is unknown. Apices of the aedeagal paraphysis are broken off in the Beaufort West specimen and the Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn specimen has the subgenital plate dismembered. The colour pattern of the crown of the 
<typeStatus id="54FC88437A65FF99FF1FFE01ED6FFE7E" box="[196,294,404,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A65FF99FEE3FE01EDD2FE7E" box="[312,411,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A65FF99FEABFE01EDD2FE7E" box="[368,411,404,429]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" unit="g" value="15.0">15g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) and Beaufort West specimen (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A65FF99FCD7FE01EF21FE7E" box="[780,872,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<date id="FFF910217A65FF99FC9FFE01EF21FE7E" box="[836,872,404,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" value="2015-01">15i</date>
</figureCitation>
) is lighter and in the Oudtshoorn specimen it is darker (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A65FF99FF36FE22ED06FE03" box="[237,335,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Fig. 15h</figureCitation>
). Styles with a medial digitate process are also found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A65FF99FC65FE2CE82BFE03" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[958,1122,441,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetracaenus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A65FF99FC65FE2CE82BFE03" box="[958,1122,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">D. tetracaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A65FF99FBB4FE22E9D5FE03" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[1135,1436,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thigmacaenus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A65FF99FBB4FE22E9D5FE03" box="[1135,1436,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Discolopeus thigmacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a similar style, but without the median digitate process. All other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A65FF99FBB3FE49E8BBFE26" authority="Stiller, 2019" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[1128,1266,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A65FF99FBB3FE49E8BBFE26" box="[1128,1266,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Discolopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have digitate, compressed or depressed style apophyses, with serrate ventral margins and sometimes a single larger apical or ventral tooth. The point distribution map of 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A65FF99FD5FFDB0EF55FDEF" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[644,796,549,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triacaenus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A65FF99FD5FFDB0EF55FDEF" box="[644,796,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">D. triacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in 
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A65FF99FC81FDB1EFF0FDEF" box="[858,953,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1496,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1466]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,193,1474]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19a–c. Distribution maps of leafhopper species of Discolopeus gen.n. and associated plants. a. Hyaenanche globosa near Vanrhynsdorp and one record near Citrusdal (red squares); b. Potential natural distribution of D. copeus sp.n. in the southwestern parts of South Africa, Western Cape Province; c. Point distributions of D. colopeus sp.n., D. lissus sp.n., D. tetracaenus sp.n., D. thigmacaenus sp.n., D. triacaenus sp.n. and D. viraktamathi sp.n. in Western, Northern and Eastern Cape Provinces." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626849/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Fig. 19c</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
